<p>aim : coordinate global taxation in times of economic digitalisation and globalisation and to reduce disputes arising out of these.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>First pillar: &nbsp;</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>allocation of taxing rights. to countries.</strong>
<ul>
<li>taxing rights over 25% of residual profits of largest MNEs would be re allocated to jurisdictions where customers of MNE reside.</li></ul></li>
<li><strong>Tax certainty via mandatory and binding dispute resolution</strong></li>
<li>&nbsp;</li></ul>
<h3>Second pillar:</h3>
<p>If companies are still able to find a way to book profits in low tax or offshore havens, countries could then apply a global minimum tax rate to be agreed upon.</p>
<p>GLoBE rules : GMCT of 15% on above 750 mn euros annual revenue&nbsp;</p>
<p>terms associated :</p>
<p>&gt;&gt; two interlocking domestic rules&nbsp; - IIR + UTPR</p>
<p>IIR = income inclusion rule&nbsp;</p>
<p>UTPR udertaxed payment rule&nbsp;</p>
<p>STTR = subject to tax rule&nbsp;</p>